AB  - There is an extensive literature on the optimal irreversible investment strategy of a solitary firm facing an exogenous price process. This paper shows that the investment strategies that this literature derives may be optimal in competitive equilibrium even though the price process is now endogenous. This provides a simple means for computing equilibrium investment strategies.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2118461
